        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-34" parent="1" style="shape=cylinder3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;boundedLbl=1;backgroundOutline=1;size=15;" value="Auth&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Database&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="60" x="1600" y="531" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-35" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=20;fontStyle=1" value="Existing solution" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="430" x="60" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-36" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;fontSize=20;fontStyle=1" value="Updated solution (proposal)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="430" x="920" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-37" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=none;dashed=1;html=1;dashPattern=8 8;strokeWidth=4;rounded=0;" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <Array as="points" />
            <mxPoint x="850" y="10" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="850" y="1090" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-38" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;fillColor=#f5f5f5;fontColor=#333333;strokeColor=#666666;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Proposed changes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;AuthService&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Make a separate Auth service, and even if applications have different Auth providers - combine Auth responsibilities into a single service. Auth Database may be presented as Database or other service (or provider).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;MainAPI&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For all the requests to main DB make a single Main API containing business logic from the clients (that may be migrated to server side).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Main API is not public, sends Auth check requests to Auth Service.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Executes queries to Main Database, sends logs to LogsDatabase (if needed).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;ReportsService&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For the reports a special Reports Service may be introduced, which will provide only the data required for reports.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Main Database may have replica(s) that can be used for reports.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;That way the team will achieve&lt;br&gt;-- a single unit for processing the requests (MainAPI) with business logic on server side. Clients are simplified, only UI and requests.&lt;br&gt;-- separated Auth logic&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-- adequate logging (if needed)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The disadvantages&lt;br&gt;-- When unified Auth Service fails - everything fails.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-- MainAPI as possible bottleneck - solved by splitting MainAPI into a couple APIs containing common logic for specific services.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-- ReportsService overhead with possible usage of Database Replica instead of DB directly.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="750" width="260" x="1750" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="wAqzE6NGV6aaY-ep7Fwl-39" parent="1" style="shape=cylinder3;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;boundedLbl=1;backgroundOutline=1;size=15;" value="Main Database" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="60" x="1590" y="327" as="geometry" />
